Taiwan Stocks: Catcher Tech, Coretronic, HTC, Motech Industries

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-06-16T05:56:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-16/taiwan-stocks-movers-china-steel-htc-nan-ya-plastics-corp-.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 1:30 p.m. close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index fell 177.02, or 2 percent, to 8,654.43, the
biggest drop since March 15.  Coretronic Corp. (5371)  (5371 TT), a liquid-crystal-display module
maker, slid 6.6 percent to NT$45, the biggest drop since Feb. 5,
2010, on declining flat-panel prices, said Cho Chih-yun, an
analyst at Mega Securities Co. Huei-Ping Wen, spokeswoman for
the company, didn’t immediately answer calls to her office.  Catcher Technology Co. (2474 TT) shares fell 6.3 percent to
NT$172, the biggest retreat since March 15, after shares of its
client  HTC Corp. (2498)  (2498 TT) slumped, said Claude Shih, an analyst
at Jih Sun Securities Co. HTC will account for at least 30
percent of Catcher’s revenue this year, Shih said. Jiun-Yi Wu, a
spokesman for Catcher, wasn’t immediately available for comment.  HTC shares sank 6.8 percent to NT$997, taking its decline
this week to 14 percent. The company was removed from UBS AG’s
list of preferred technology stocks, according to a report dated
yesterday. Macquarie Group Ltd. cut HTC to “neutral” from
“outperform” yesterday.  Motech Industries Ltd. (6244 TT), a solar-cell maker,
gained 3.8 percent to NT$102, the most since May 31, on
speculation  Taiwan ’s government may announce policies tomorrow
promoting the use of clean energy, said Charlie Yeh, an analyst
at President Securities Corp. Wang Yunn-ming, deputy director-
general at the island’s Bureau of Energy, wasn’t immediately
available for comment at his office and hasn’t replied to
messages left for him.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Weiyi Lim in Singapore at 
 wlim26@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
